<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-23T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="70" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/422</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-23T18:00:00+01:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received April 24, 3.25
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9673. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                            <p>No. 471. Your 343, April 16, Department’s 7302, and your 375, April
                                22, Department’s 7369.<note n="1" xml:id="d70fn1">The latter not
                                    printed.</note> British, French, and Italian representatives are
                                authorized to extend relaxation of embargo on nonessentials to
                                Norway and Denmark and only await your approval to determine date on
                                which to make same operative. Understand that possibility reopening
                                negotiations with representatives of Denmark might make it
                                inadvisable extend relaxation to Denmark at present but would
                                inquire if you approve regarding Norway.<note n="2" xml:id="d70fn2">The reply of May 4, Department’s No. 7570, War Trade Board’s
                                    No. 428, states: “We have approved the extension of the
                                    relaxation of the embargo on non-essentials to Denmark. … Norway
                                    of course is not considered in this connection in view of the
                                    recent conclusion of the agreement with her.” (File No.
                                    657.119/422.)</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>